// H9a acceptance area (d) — a params loom forcing a real binder pass.
// Two `params:` fields (one defaulted) route to the binder (NOT a bypass), so a
// genuine binder pass over the declared params runs before the body and streams
// the three-arm binder envelope JSON as its user-visible turn. The body is a
// pure-literal `respond`, which drives no streamed turn, so nothing else prints
// a JSON object around the envelope.
respond "ok"
